---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "@/config/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy — Thejands"
  description="Thejands uses minimal browser storage. No advertising cookies, no cross-site tracking. Vercel Edge Analytics sets no cookies. Full details here."
  keywords="Thejands cookie policy, cookies, browser storage, Vercel Analytics, no tracking"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: "Home", item: "https://thejands.in" },
    { name: "Cookie Policy", item: "https://thejands.in/cookies" },
  ]}
>
  <article
    class="section-spacing mx-auto max-w-[var(--max-width-content)] px-6"
  >
    <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-ink mt-0">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-body-sm text-mute">Last updated: 23 May 2026</p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      This Cookie Policy explains how Thejands uses cookies and similar
      browser-side storage technologies on <a
        href="https://thejands.in"
        class="underline underline-offset-4">thejands.in</a
      >. We have designed this website to be as privacy-preserving as possible:
      we use no advertising cookies, no cross-site tracking, and no third-party
      analytics that set cookies in your browser.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      This policy should be read alongside our <a
        href="/privacy"
        class="underline underline-offset-4">Privacy Policy</a
      >, which explains how we handle personal data more broadly.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      1. What Are Cookies?
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Cookies are small text files that a website places in your browser when
      you visit. They are widely used to make websites function, remember your
      preferences, and — in many commercial contexts — to track your behaviour
      across multiple sites for advertising purposes.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      There are also related browser-side storage technologies, including <code
        >localStorage</code
      > and <code>sessionStorage</code>, which work similarly but are stored
      differently within your browser and cannot be read by other sites. We use <code
        >localStorage</code
      > in one limited context, described below.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Cookies and local storage can be set by the domain you are visiting
      ("first-party") or by third-party services embedded in the page. We only
      set first-party storage, and only for a single functional purpose.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      2. How Thejands Uses Browser Storage
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      We keep our use of browser storage to an absolute minimum. Here is what we
      store and why:
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      Cookie Consent Preference
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      When you interact with our cookie consent notice, your preference
      (accepted or declined) is saved using the browser's <code
        >localStorage</code
      > API under the key <code>cookie-consent</code>. This ensures you are not
      shown the consent notice on every page visit.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      This is a <strong>localStorage entry, not a cookie</strong>. It is stored
      locally in your browser, is never transmitted to our servers, and cannot
      be read by any third party. It contains no personally identifiable
      information — only a preference flag and a timestamp.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      Browser Session State
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Your browser itself may create session-level storage entries as part of
      normal HTTP operation (for example, to maintain a connection). These are
      managed entirely by your browser and are cleared when you close the
      browser tab or session. Thejands does not control or access this data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      3. Vercel Analytics — No Cookies Set
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      This website uses Vercel Analytics to understand aggregate traffic
      patterns. Vercel Analytics is fundamentally different from tools like
      Google Analytics:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        <strong>No cookies are set.</strong> Vercel Analytics does not place any cookie
        — first-party or third-party — in your browser.
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        <strong>Edge-based processing only.</strong> Analytics data is derived from
        anonymised network request information processed at Vercel's edge infrastructure
        — it never reaches a client-side script running in your browser.
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        <strong>No cross-site tracking.</strong> There is no tracking pixel, beacon,
        or identifier that follows you across sites.
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        <strong>No personal data retained.</strong> We receive only aggregated, anonymised
        metrics such as page views per day and approximate visitor geography at country
        level. No individual visitor is identifiable.
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        <strong>No fingerprinting.</strong> Vercel does not use browser fingerprinting
        techniques to identify or re-identify visitors.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Because Vercel Analytics sets no cookies and processes no personal data,
      it does not require your consent under GDPR, UK GDPR, or ePrivacy rules.
      We include this information here for full transparency.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      4. No Third-Party Advertising or Tracking Cookies
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Thejands does not use — and has never used — any of the following on this
      website:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Google Analytics or Google Tag Manager tracking cookies
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Meta (Facebook) Pixel or any social network tracking pixel
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        LinkedIn Insight Tag or advertising retargeting
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        HubSpot, Salesforce, Marketo, or any CRM tracking cookie
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Any advertising network, demand-side platform, or programmatic
        advertising cookie
      </li>
      <li class="mt-2 text-body-md text-body">
        Any cross-site identity resolution or data broker integration
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      We are an enterprise B2B firm that earns clients through reputation and
      relationships, not through retargeted advertising. Our commitment to
      privacy is practical as well as principled.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      5. Cookie Categories Summary
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      The table below summarises all categories of cookies and browser storage
      used on this site:
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-hairline">
            <th class="py-3 pr-6 font-display text-heading-sm text-ink"
              >Category</th
            >
            <th class="py-3 pr-6 font-display text-heading-sm text-ink"
              >What We Use</th
            >
            <th class="py-3 pr-6 font-display text-heading-sm text-ink"
              >Storage Type</th
            >
            <th class="py-3 font-display text-heading-sm text-ink"
              >Consent Required?</th
            >
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-hairline">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-md text-ink font-medium"
              >Strictly Necessary</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body"
              >Consent preference (<code>cookie-consent</code>); browser session
              state</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body"
              >localStorage; browser-native</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 text-body-sm text-body">No — functional only</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-hairline">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-md text-ink font-medium"
              >Performance / Analytics</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body"
              >Vercel Edge Analytics — anonymised, no cookie set</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body">None (edge only)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-body-sm text-body">No — no personal data</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-hairline">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-md text-ink font-medium"
              >Functional</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body">None</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body">—</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-body-sm text-body">—</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-md text-ink font-medium"
              >Targeting / Advertising</td
            >
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body">None</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-body-sm text-body">—</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-body-sm text-body">—</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      6. Managing Cookies and Browser Storage
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Because we set no tracking or advertising cookies, there is very little to
      manage. However, you have full control over your browser's storage at all
      times:
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      Clearing localStorage
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      You can clear all localStorage data for this site (including the <code
        >cookie-consent</code
      > key) through your browser's developer tools or privacy settings. The exact
      steps vary by browser — look for "Site data", "Storage", or "Clear browsing
      data" in your browser's settings. Clearing this will reset your consent preference,
      and you will see the consent notice again on your next visit.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      Browser Cookie Settings
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      All modern browsers allow you to view, block, and delete cookies through
      their privacy and security settings. Since we set no cookies, adjusting
      these settings will have no material effect on your experience of this
      website. Blocking cookies will not prevent you from using any feature on
      thejands.in.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">Do Not Track</h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Some browsers offer a "Do Not Track" (DNT) signal. We do not track users
      regardless of this signal, so enabling DNT will not change your experience
      on this site. We respect the spirit of DNT as a matter of principle, not
      just compliance.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-heading-sm text-ink mt-6">
      Vercel Analytics Opt-Out
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      Because Vercel Analytics processes anonymised network-level data with no
      cookies and no personal identifiers, there is no individual opt-out
      mechanism. The data is not attributable to you as an individual. If you
      use a VPN, your approximate geography will reflect the VPN exit node
      rather than your actual location — Vercel Analytics cannot distinguish
      this and we do not attempt to.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">
      7. Future Changes
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      If we ever introduce new cookies or storage technologies — for example, to
      support a client portal, authentication system, or new analytics tool — we
      will update this policy before doing so, refresh the "Last updated" date,
      and ensure appropriate consent mechanisms are in place. We are committed
      to transparency about any such changes.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      We review this Cookie Policy at least annually and whenever we make
      changes to the technical infrastructure of this website.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-heading-lg text-ink mt-10">8. Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      If you have any questions about this Cookie Policy or about how we handle
      browser data, please get in touch:
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      <strong>Thejands</strong><br />
      Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India<br />
      Email: <a
        href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contact.email}`}
        class="underline underline-offset-4">{siteConfig.contact.email}</a
      >
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-body-md text-body">
      For broader data protection questions, please refer to our <a
        href="/privacy"
        class="underline underline-offset-4">Privacy Policy</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
